<subSubSection id="C351651EFF91EE75FF16FB00F4932D8B" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" type="key">
<key id="FFDA61A4FF91EE75FF16FB00F4932D8B" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<keyStep id="30BF2E30FF91EE75FF16FB00F4922EAB" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<paragraph id="8BF43695FF91EE75FF16FB00F4932E6B" blockId="3.[192,1441,1256,1691]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30BA95A0FF91EE75FF16FB00F4932E6B" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
1. First joint of labial palps as long as second (
<figureCitation id="13702A10FF91EE75FCFFFB00F2992FEB" box="[809,938,1256,1275]" captionStart="Figure 43-56" captionStartId="35.[192,279,1783,1800]" captionTargetBox="[281,1342,219,1634]" captionTargetId="figure-80@35.[264,1368,192,1754]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="Figure 43-56. Gonaphodiellus opisthius (Bates, 1887) (Zacualtipan, Hidalgo, Mexico). 43) Epipharynx. 44- 47) Habitus (length ideogram, color variations and morphological details). 48-49) Aedeagus (dorsal and lateral view). 50) Right labial palp (dorsal view). Gonaphodiellus pacatus (Harold, 1880) (Tolima, Rovira, Colombia). 51) Labial palp. 52) Epipharynx. 53-54) Habitus (morphological details and length ideogram). 55-56) Aedeagus (dorsal and lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5174230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5174230/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Fig. 50-51</figureCitation>
); clypeus subtruncate anteriorly or very feebly sinuate at middle, round at sides; elytra oval, more or less broadened posteriorly, finely striate; body feebly or, at most, moderately convex; mostly medium size species (length 5.0- 6.0 mm). Taxa more or less dark brownish, with or without paler elytral spots. Neotropical region ................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B4D16FF91EE75FB92FA80F4932E6B" authority="Schmidt" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1913" box="[1092,1440,1384,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gonaphodiellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93FEA87FF91EE75FB92FA80F4932E6B" bold="true" box="[1092,1440,1384,1403]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="B93FEA87FF91EE75FB92FA80F4172E6B" bold="true" box="[1092,1316,1384,1403]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Gonaphodiellus</emphasis>
Schmidt
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF43695FF91EE75FF16FA60F4922EAB" blockId="3.[192,1441,1256,1691]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30BA95A0FF91EE75FF16FA60F4922EAB" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
— First joint of labial palps longer than second (
<figureCitation id="13702A10FF91EE75FC87FA60F29F2E8B" box="[849,940,1416,1435]" captionStart="Figure 67-77" captionStartId="37.[192,278,1783,1800]" captionTargetBox="[285,1308,192,1660]" captionTargetId="figure-82@37.[264,1368,192,1754]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Figure 67-77. Gonaphodioides acutecernans (Balthasar, 1960) (Cochabamba Prov., Bolivia). 67) Epipharynx. 68, 70) Habitus (length ideogram and morphological details). 69) Right labial palp (dorsal view). 71-72) Aedeagus (dorsal and lateral view). Gonaphodioides chapini (Hinton, 1934) (2 Km N Sta. Clara, W Hartmann’s Finca, Chiriqui Prov., Panama). 73) Epipharynx. 74-75) Habitus (morphological details and length ideogram). 76-77) Aedeagus (dorsal and lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5174234" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5174234/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Fig. 69</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13702A10FF91EE75FC6FFA60F2DA2E8B" box="[953,1001,1416,1435]" captionStart="Figure 109-119" captionStartId="41.[192,279,1783,1800]" captionTargetBox="[306,1315,216,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-87@41.[264,1368,192,1754]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Figure 109-119. Gonaphodiopsis hypogea, new species (Salamander Cave, Rancho del Cielo, Gomes Farias, Tamaulipas, Mexico). 109) Epipharynx. 110-111) Habitus (length ideogram and morphological details). 112- 113) Aedeagus (dorsal and lateral view). Gonaphodiopsis montesdeocai, new species (Xuatusco env., Parada de los Pinos, Veracruz, Mexico). 114) Epipharynx. 115-116) Habitus (morphological details and length ideogram). 117) Right labial palp (dorsal view). 118-119) Aedeagus (dorsal and lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5174242" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5174242/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">117</figureCitation>
); body more convex; mostly rather small species (length 4.0-5.0 mm) .............................................................................................. 
<emphasis id="B93FEA87FF91EE75FA44FA40F4922EAB" bold="true" box="[1426,1441,1448,1467]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">2</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30BF2E30FF91EE75FF16FA00F4932D8B" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<paragraph id="8BF43695FF91EE75FF16FA00F4932D2B" blockId="3.[192,1441,1256,1691]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30BA95A0FF91EE75FF16FA00F4932D2B" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
2(1). Clypeus deeply sinuate at middle, angulate at sides; elytra subparallel-sided or oval elongate, finely striate; body more or less distinctly convex. Taxa chestnut brown or reddish testaceous, rarely blackish. Neotropical region ........................................... 
<emphasis id="B93FEA87FF91EE75FBF4F9C0F4932D2B" bold="true" box="[1058,1440,1576,1595]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName id="4C4B4D16FF91EE75FBF4F9C0F4352D2B" authority="Dellacasa &amp; Dellacasa &amp; Gordon, 2012" authorityName="Dellacasa &amp; Dellacasa &amp; Gordon" authorityYear="2012" box="[1058,1286,1576,1595]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gonaphodioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis id="B93FEA87FF91EE75FBF4F9C0F4352D2B" bold="true" box="[1058,1286,1576,1595]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Gonaphodioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20C57FCFF91EE75FADAF9C0F4932D2B" box="[1292,1440,1576,1595]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" rank="genus">new genus</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF43695FF91EE75FF16F9A0F4932D8B" blockId="3.[192,1441,1256,1691]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30BA95A0FF91EE75FF16F9A0F4932D8B" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
— Clypeus feebly sinuate at middle, round at sides; elytra amygdaliform, deeply striate; body strongly convex. Taxa piceous or reddish brown, usually with pronotum and elytral disc darker. 
<collectingCountry id="F35C7605FF91EE75FEF6F960F0452D8B" box="[288,374,1672,1691]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Mexico</collectingCountry>
........................................................................................... 
<emphasis id="B93FEA87FF91EE75FBF0F960F4932D8B" bold="true" box="[1062,1440,1672,1691]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName id="4C4B4D16FF91EE75FBF0F960F4342D8B" authority="Dellacasa &amp; Dellacasa &amp; Gordon, 2012" authorityName="Dellacasa &amp; Dellacasa &amp; Gordon" authorityYear="2012" box="[1062,1287,1672,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Aphodiidae" genus="Gonaphodiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis id="B93FEA87FF91EE75FBF0F960F4342D8B" bold="true" box="[1062,1287,1672,1691]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Gonaphodiopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20C57FCFF91EE75FADBF960F4932D8B" box="[1293,1440,1672,1691]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" rank="genus">new genus</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
